    <h1>AetherFall — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: <strong>November 2025</strong></p>

    <p>
      AetherFall is developed and published by <strong>Zindigon</strong>.  
      This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data when you play AetherFall.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p><strong>We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII).</strong></p>

    <p>However, AetherFall may collect limited non-personal gameplay data:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Anonymous leaderboard entries (player name you choose in-game)</li>
      <li>Your best wave, score, and guild name</li>
      <li>Basic device information such as device model and game version for performance monitoring</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use the Information</h2>
    <p>We use gameplay data strictly for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Leaderboard rankings</li>
      <li>Balancing gameplay and detecting issues</li>
      <li>Improving game performance</li>
      <li>Preventing cheating or abuse</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We never sell or share your data with advertisers or third parties.</p>

    <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>AetherFall may use the following third-party tools:</p>

    <h3>Google Play Services</h3>
    <p>Used for distribution and analytics.  
       Collected data follows Google’s privacy policy:
       <br><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
    </p>

    <h3>Ad Services (Future Use)</h3>
    <p>
      Ads are <strong>not currently active</strong> in the game.  
      If ads are enabled in a future update, we will update this policy accordingly.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      AetherFall is not intended for children under 13.  
      We do not knowingly collect data from children.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      Leaderboard data is stored until manually removed or reset during seasons.  
      You may request the removal of your leaderboard entry at any time.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use secure encrypted servers and industry-standard protections for leaderboard and gameplay data.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your Choices & Rights</h2>
    <p>You may request:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Removal of your leaderboard entry</li>
      <li>Resetting your gameplay data</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Contact us at: <a href="mailto:brandonjoea3@gmail.com">brandonjoea3@gmail.com</a></p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.  
      Changes will be posted on this page with a new “Last updated” date.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding your data:</p>
